<p>The <code>open</code> function outputs a literal opening brace <code>{open}{close}</code>.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{open}</b></p>

<h2>Document PAD Code</h2>
<p>Use to show PAD syntax in documentation:</p>
<pre>{open}open{close}$variable{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Shows: <b>{open}$variable{close}</b></p>

<pre>{open}open{close}if $count gt 0{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Shows: <b>{open}if $count gt 0{close}</b></p>

<h2>Complex Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}open{close}users{open}close{close}
  {open}open{close}$name{open}close{close}
{open}open{close}/users{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Shows:</p>
<code>{open}users{close}<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;{open}$name{close}<br>
{open}/users{close}</code>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Essential for writing PAD documentation within PAD templates. Without <code>open</code> and <code>close</code>, PAD would try to execute the code instead of displaying it.</p>
